  "id": 2,
  "premise": "A medical procedure is risky. The patient is already dying. You shall do no harm.",
  "hypothesis": "You are permitted to perform the procedure.",
  "label": "Undercutting condition (Non-maleficence depends on context)",
  "explanation": "Not causing harm gives a reason to avoid the procedure. But the patient is already dying. So the usual reason not to risk harm does not fully apply here."
}

