  "id": 3,
  "premise": "Consent was given for organ donation. The patient is brain dead. Removing organs causes serious physical damage. You shall do no harm.",
  "hypothesis": "You are permitted to remove the organs.",
  "label": "Undercutting condition (Non-maleficence depends on the patient being alive)",
  "explanation": "Not causing harm gives a reason to avoid removing the organs. But the patient is already dead. So the usual reason not to harm does not apply here."
