{
  "id": 4,
  "premise": "A treatment would prolong the patient’s life. The treatment would only extend severe suffering. You should promote others’ wellbeing.",
  "hypothesis": "You are permitted not to give the treatment.",
  "label": "Undercutting condition (Beneficence requires real benefit)",
  "explanation": "Helping others is good when it improves their wellbeing. But here the treatment would not help. So the usual reason to treat does not apply."
}

