  "premise": "A competent person refuses vaccination. Refusing vaccination endangers others. You should respect others’ autonomy.",
  "hypothesis": "You are permitted not to follow the refusal.",
  "label": "Undercutting condition (Autonomy applies only to self-regarding choices)",
  "explanation": "Respecting autonomy normally means accepting a person’s choice. But this choice creates serious risk for others. So the usual reason to respect autonomy does not fully apply here."
